        <mxCell id="legend" value="Flow:&#10;1. User &#8594; Front Door (HTTPS, custom domain)&#10;2. Front Door &#8594; F5 Public VIP (origin = public DNS A-record to F5 PIP)&#10;3. F5 hairpin to Palo Alto for L7 inspection (TLS terminate or pass-through)&#10;4. F5 NATs source to its trust IP, destination to Spoke PE private IP (via VNet peering)&#10;5. Private Link &#8594; Web App (App Service publicNetworkAccess=Disabled)&#10;6. Web App &#8594; Key Vault using Managed Identity (token issued by Entra ID)&#10;&#10;Architectural notes:&#10;&#8226; Public IP is associated with the F5 BIG-IP&#39;s untrust NIC (drawn adjacent to F5 to make the association explicit).&#10;&#8226; Private DNS zone privatelink.azurewebsites.net is linked to the Hub VNet so F5 can resolve the PE FQDN to its private IP.&#10;&#8226; Web App custom-domain binding must match AFD&#39;s custom domain so the host header passes through cleanly.&#10;&#8226; Hub-spoke VNet peering is required for F5 to reach the spoke PE private IP.&#10;&#8226; In production, F5 typically has untrust + trust NICs (in separate subnets) and Palo Alto similarly. The single-icon-per-NVA shown here is a high-level simplification; for detailed designs split each NVA across two subnets."
          style="text;html=1;strokeColor=#CCCCCC;fillColor=#FAFAFA;align=left;verticalAlign=top;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;fontSize=11;fontColor=#444444;spacingTop=8;spacingLeft=10;spacingRight=10;spacingBottom=8;"
          vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="40" y="950" width="1820" height="280" as="geometry"/>
        </mxCell>

